Requirement is not verified 0x150190 - Virtuelles Pedal Türöffnung Fahrerseite hinten unplausible Botschaft
When the software receives from the GW signal:
Each transmission message of LIN slaves is individually monitored by the LIN master - Event triggered frames are ignored.
If the LIN master for time TQ recognizes one or more (but not all) transmission frames of a LIN slaves as missing or one, more or all transmission frames as faulty, the DTC 0x150190 shall be set as Qualified.
Failure criteria: - LIN slave sends set Response Error bit due to errors in the transmitting or receiving frames - LIN master receives one, several or all the transmission frames of a Slaves faulty (wrong checksum / false DLC)
Event log entry is not triggered IF: - LIN slave sends the defined signal value "error" in one or multiple signals
If the LIN frame of the control unit received correctly (fully && checksum I.O.), it shall set the DTC 0x150190 as Not Qualified.
Note: Precondition: Bus "LIN-Energie"==active && s_NWDF*==1.
Only valid if the conditions for "Local data error electrical error" and "Local data bus no communication" on the same LIN bus segment and "Slave no communication" for the same LIN slave are not met.
VIP HFS coded ID: SWR_ICAS1_GW_22767 _ObjectType: Requirement SPR: not_SPR_reviewed ASIL: QM
